From the POLEN23E dataset, five images of each pollen type were used for the training set, which comprised 115 images altogether. The volunteers were allowed to examine the support material (see S3 Text ), while classifying the images, as shown in the questionnaire ( Fig 4 ). In this material, the pollen common names were used because these are easier to memorize than their respective scientific names. The questionnaire also contained an open question where the users could write down the visual features that they analyzed in order to classify a pollen grain and the most difficult aspects of the classification process.
